Find the century anchor. Starting with year 2026:
 - take the century digits C = Y / 100 = 2026 / 100 = 20
 - in a four century cycle its index is F = C % 4 = 20 % 4 = 0
 - the resulting increment is I = F * 5 = 0 * 5 = 0 ≡ Sunday
 - add Tuesday and get A = Tuesday + I = Tuesday + Sunday = 2 ≡ Tuesday

Find the year anchor. Starting with year 2026:
 - note the century anchor A = Tuesday
 - take the last two digits T = Y % 100 = 2026 % 100 = 26
 - divide them by twelve D = T / 12 = 26 / 12 = 2
 - and take the reminder R = T % 12 = 26 % 12 = 2
 - the resulting increment is I = (D + R) + R/4 = (2 + 2) + 2/4 = 4 ≡ Thursday
 - add the century anchor to get W = A + I = Tuesday + Thursday = 6 ≡ Saturday

Find the weekday. Starting with date 27 February 2026:
 - note the year anchor W = Saturday
 - this months doomsday is O = 28 (the last day of February)
 - the resulting increment is I = D - O = 27 - 28 = -1 ≡ Saturday
 - add the year anchor to get R = W + I = Saturday + Saturday = 12 ≡ Friday
The weekday is Friday.